summary:
Hi! My name is Filipe Lopes, Portuguese, living in Amersfoort together with my girlfriend and our three kids (11, 9 and 2 yo). Enjoying the Netherlands at its best, my family and I share the love for sports, arts, science and technology. They made me become a dynamic, persistent, problem-solving person, also loyal and supportive, qualities that I take to work every day.

I am an experienced Technology Specialist / Process Engineer / Researcher in Chemical and Environmental Engineering with a demonstrated history of working with sustainable development.

𝗧𝗲𝗰𝗵𝗻𝗶𝗰𝗮𝗹 𝘀𝗸𝗶𝗹𝗹𝘀
▫ Chemical & Environmental Engineering: assessment of materials’ interaction, degradation and activity under controlled laboratory, harsh and realistic conditions (off- and onsite pilot and full-scale);
▫ Process Engineering & Technology: design of (conceptual) reaction, separation, purification and treatment processes; Improvement of current technologies; development of models for data simulation;
▫ Material Science: development of new methods for adsorbent/catalyst synthesis and characterization;
▫ Project Management Engineering: networking, business case definition, project initiation, planning, coordination & lead, commissioning and start-up, reporting and project management.

𝗦𝗰𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗶𝗳𝗶𝗰 𝗶𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘁𝘀
▫ Chemical & Environmental Engineering; Process Technology; Process Engineering;
▫ Reaction, Separation, Purification & Treatment Processes: heterogeneous catalysis, cyclic separation and purification processes (e.g. adsorption/PSA, membrane/NF/RO), wastewater treatment processes (e.g. biotreatment, MBR, SBR, DAF), advanced oxidation processes (e.g. UV/H2O2/Cat).

𝗣𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 𝘀𝗸𝗶𝗹𝗹𝘀
▫ Sociability and empathy; Analysis, structure and work style; Drive and communication.

profile_positions.description:
𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗷𝗲𝗰𝘁 𝗠𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗘𝘅𝗰𝗲𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲 - 𝗘𝗻𝘃𝗶𝗿𝗼𝗻𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗮𝗹 𝗧𝗲𝗰𝗵𝗻𝗼𝗹𝗼𝗴𝘆 (𝗣𝗠𝗘-𝗘𝗧)
▫ Coordination & Lead of various research projects and workstreams, providing high quality and sustainable environmental technology solutions for Nouryon Integrated Supply Chain (ISC);
▫ Identification of new sustainable projects (incl. scope definition, planning, etc.);
▫ Support on BROC and Growth Nouryon Projects: project initiation; technical specification, vendor selection and evaluation; commissioning and start-up; standard operating procedures;
▫ Support of Nouryon ISC regions, sites, projects, Businesses with regard to (new)environmental technology issues and identification of new opportunities;
▫ Provide consultancy on anticipating, measuring & complying with permits, standards and other requirements.

𝗘𝘅𝗽𝗲𝗿𝘁 𝗖𝗮𝗽𝗮𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗚𝗿𝗼𝘂𝗽 - 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗰𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗧𝗲𝗰𝗵𝗻𝗼𝗹𝗼𝗴𝘆 (𝗘𝗖𝗚-𝗣𝗧)
▫ Coordination & Lead of various research projects and workstreams to deliver projects in process technology for several Nouryon Businesses;
▫ Process control and optimization; data handling and analysis for improvement of current processes;
▫ Development of new technologies and sustainable processes for the different Nouryon Businesses;
▫ Design of experiments and off- and onsite pilot trials, and set up operating procedures;
▫ Support HAZOP/5S/BBS studies.

𝗖𝗮𝘁𝗮𝗹𝘆𝘀𝗶𝘀 𝗘𝗻𝗴𝗶𝗻𝗲𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴 (𝗖𝗘) 𝗥𝗲𝘀𝗲𝗮𝗿𝗰𝗵 𝗚𝗿𝗼𝘂𝗽, 𝗖𝗵𝗲𝗺𝗘, 𝗧𝗨 𝗗𝗲𝗹𝗳𝘁
▫ Upgrade of a six fixed-bed parallel gas-phase unit for ethanol conversion into bulk chemicals (GC analysis);
▫ Design & synthesis (wet-kneading and atomic layer deposition) of several magnesia-silica catalysts;
▫ Characterization and assessment of materials' interaction, degradation, activity and long term performance; 
▫ Study of the most adequate reactor configuration based on the kinetic modelling studies.
𝘙&𝘋: "𝘊𝘢𝘵𝘤𝘩𝘉𝘪𝘰 – 𝘊𝘢𝘵𝘢𝘭𝘺𝘴𝘪𝘴 𝘧𝘰𝘳 𝘚𝘶𝘴𝘵𝘢𝘪𝘯𝘢𝘣𝘭𝘦 𝘊𝘩𝘦𝘮𝘪𝘤𝘢𝘭𝘴 𝘧𝘳𝘰𝘮 𝘉𝘪𝘰𝘮𝘢𝘴𝘴"

𝗔𝘀𝘀𝗼𝗰𝗶𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝗟𝗮𝗯𝗼𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗼𝗿𝘆 𝗟𝗦𝗥𝗘/𝗟𝗖𝗠, 𝗙𝗘𝗨𝗣 - 𝗙𝗮𝗰𝘂𝗹𝘁𝘆 𝗼𝗳 𝗘𝗻𝗴𝗶𝗻𝗲𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴, 𝗨𝗻𝗶𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗼𝗳 𝗣𝗼𝗿𝘁𝗼 (𝗣𝗼𝗿𝘁𝘂𝗴𝗮𝗹)
▫ Catalyst synthesis: doped titania, photocatalytic inks, water-based vinyl inks, etc;
▫ Conceptual design of catalysts’ supports and reactor configuration (sol-gel, dip-coating, etc.);
▫ Characterization: SEM, TEM, EDX, XRD, XPS, GC-MS, N2 adsorption, UV-Vis absorption;
▫ Design & construction of a lab-scale photoreactor for inactivation of microorganisms and degradation of volatile organic compounds (VOCs) and a low-cost photoreactor prototype for continuous operation;
𝘙&𝘋: "𝘚𝘰𝘭𝘢𝘳 𝘗𝘩𝘰𝘵𝘰𝘤𝘢𝘵𝘢𝘭𝘺𝘵𝘪𝘤 𝘛𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘵𝘮𝘦𝘯𝘵 𝘰𝘧 𝘐𝘯𝘥𝘰𝘰𝘳 𝘈𝘪𝘳" 𝘢𝘯𝘥 "𝘈𝘐𝘙𝘗𝘏𝘖𝘛𝘖𝘟𝘐 – 𝘚𝘰𝘭𝘢𝘳 𝘐𝘯𝘥𝘰𝘰𝘳 𝘈𝘪𝘳 𝘋𝘦𝘵𝘰𝘹𝘪𝘧𝘪𝘤𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯: 𝘉𝘪𝘰𝘢𝘦𝘳𝘰𝘴𝘰𝘭𝘴 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘝𝘖𝘊𝘴"

𝗔𝘀𝘀𝗼𝗰𝗶𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝗟𝗮𝗯𝗼𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗼𝗿𝘆 𝗟𝗦𝗥𝗘/𝗟𝗖𝗠, 𝗙𝗘𝗨𝗣 - 𝗙𝗮𝗰𝘂𝗹𝘁𝘆 𝗼𝗳 𝗘𝗻𝗴𝗶𝗻𝗲𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴, 𝗨𝗻𝗶𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗼𝗳 𝗣𝗼𝗿𝘁𝗼 (𝗣𝗼𝗿𝘁𝘂𝗴𝗮𝗹)
▫ Synthesis, characterization & testing: carbon-based and zeolite materials;
▫ Generation of adsorption data for different gas mixtures (H2, CO2, CO, N2, etc.) in adsorbent materials;
▫ Design & upgrade of an experimental pressure swing adsorption (PSA) facility, coupling a new GC analysis system able to determine the composition of several H2/CO2 multicomponent gas mixtures;
▫ Design of new cyclic processes for gas separation and purification.
𝘙&𝘋: “𝘏𝘠2𝘚𝘌𝘗𝘚 – 𝘏𝘺𝘣𝘳𝘪𝘥 𝘏𝘺𝘥𝘳𝘰𝘨𝘦𝘯 - 𝘊𝘢𝘳𝘣𝘰𝘯 𝘋𝘪𝘰𝘹𝘪𝘥𝘦 𝘚𝘦𝘱𝘢𝘳𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯 𝘚𝘺𝘴𝘵𝘦𝘮𝘴” 𝘢𝘯𝘥 "𝘕𝘦𝘸 𝘱𝘳𝘦𝘴𝘴𝘶𝘳𝘦 𝘴𝘸𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘢𝘥𝘴𝘰𝘳𝘱𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯 𝘤𝘺𝘤𝘭𝘦𝘴 𝘧𝘰𝘳 𝘩𝘺𝘥𝘳𝘰𝘨𝘦𝘯 𝘱𝘶𝘳𝘪𝘧𝘪𝘤𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯 𝘧𝘳𝘰𝘮 𝘴𝘵𝘦𝘢𝘮 𝘮𝘦𝘵𝘩𝘢𝘯𝘦 𝘳𝘦𝘧𝘰𝘳𝘮𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘰𝘧𝘧-𝘨𝘢𝘴𝘦𝘴"
